  <h2>Blog Related to Taj Mahal</h2>
  <pre>The Taj Mahal, located in Agra, India, is one of the most iconic symbols of love in the world. 
       Built by Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his wife Mumtaz Mahal, this white marble masterpiece attracts millions of visitors every year.
       Its symmetrical gardens, intricate carvings, and changing colors at sunrise and sunset create a magical experience.
       The Taj Mahal is not just a monument but a timeless expression of devotion,craftsmanship, and architectural brilliance.</pre>>
  <h2>Blog Related to Paris</h2>
  <pre>Paris, known as the “City of Love,” is famous for its romantic charm, historic monuments, and artistic heritage.
  Attractions like the Eiffel Tower, Louvre Museum, and charming cafés along the Seine make Paris a dream destination. 
  The city is also a fashion and culinary capital, offering world-class shopping and cuisine.
  Walking through Paris feels like stepping into a living museum filled with elegance, culture, and timeless beauty.</pre>>
  <h2>Blog Related to Cape Town</h2>
  <pre>Cape Town is one of the most scenic cities in the world, surrounded by mountains, beaches, and ocean views.
  Table Mountain, Cape Point, and nearby vineyards make it a paradise for nature lovers and photographers. 
  The city is rich in history, culture, and biodiversity, offering a relaxed yet adventurous atmosphere.
  Cape Town’s natural beauty and vibrant lifestyle create a memorable experience for every visitor.</pre>>
  <h2>Blog Related to New York City</h2>
  <pre>New York City, often called “The City That Never Sleeps,” is a global hub of culture, finance, and entertainment. 
  Landmarks like Times Square, Central Park, and the Statue of Liberty define its dynamic character. 
  The city’s diversity is reflected in its neighborhoods, food, art, and music scenes. 
  Whether it’s Broadway shows, towering skyscrapers, or vibrant street life, New York City offers unforgettable experiences at every corner.</pre>>
  <h2>Blog Related to Dubai</h2>
  <pre>Dubai is a city of luxury, innovation, and futuristic architecture rising from the desert.
  Known for landmarks like Burj Khalifa, Palm Jumeirah, and vast shopping malls, Dubai showcases rapid development and modern lifestyle.
  Along with luxury, the city also offers cultural experiences through traditional souks, desert safaris, and Emirati heritage sites. 
  Dubai perfectly combines tradition with modern ambition, making it a unique global destination.</pre>>
  <h2>Blog Related to Tokyo</h2>
  <pre>Tokyo is a fascinating city where ancient traditions blend seamlessly with cutting-edge technology.
  From peaceful temples like Senso-ji to vibrant districts such as Shibuya and Akihabara, Tokyo offers something for every traveler. 
  The city is famous for its efficient transport system, delicious cuisine like sushi and ramen, and seasonal beauty, 
  especially during cherry blossom season. Tokyo’s energy, cleanliness, and innovation make it one of the most exciting cities in the world.</pre>
